In a bid to encourage interest in Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics (STEM), Medplus Pharmacy Nigeria partnered with STEM in Africa (SIA) at its just-concluded conference, themed “Identifying and Breaking Barriers”. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-818812 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-1.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="683" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-1.jpg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-1-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"> The conference focused on promoting interest in science through exciting experiments and workshops for disadvantaged children. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-818814 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-2-1.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="683" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-2-1.jpg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-2-1-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px">  It was held simultaneously at three different locations – Medplus Pharmacy Lekki, CIS Lekki and Connoisseurs Ikoyi – on July 16, 2020.  With the continuous expansion of STEM in the 21st century, SIA’s stated mission is majorly to help and empower young people on the continent and build the next generation of leaders, as science and technology plays a key role in sustaining growth and stability of all economies. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-818815 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-3.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="681" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-3.jpg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-3-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"> The STEM2020 conference is envisioned to create more opportunities in STEM and serve as a boost to the innovation ecosystem in Nigeria. At the event, Marketing Manager, Medplus Pharmacy Nigeria, Senami Atika, explained that Medplus is not just committed to helping their customers feel or look good but the brand is also committed to create opportunities for those excluded by social disadvantages. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-818816 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-4.jpg" alt="" width="681" height="1024" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-4.jpg 681w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-4-200x300.jpg 200w" sizes="(max-width: 681px) 100vw, 681px"> “As we are all are getting used to the new normal, the importance of STEM has become very significant especially in the 21st century where scientific and technological innovations are the order of the day and it is very important to support kids to develop capabilities in STEM skills as it required to compete in a global economy. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-818817 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-5.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="681" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-5.jpg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-5-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"> “We are happy to partner with SIA and its even more exciting to see the kid’s reactions during the experiments and the brand look forward to doing more of these in the future”, Atika said. Fara Bakare, SIA Founder, said based on his relentless commitment to the course, he had the urge to carry on with the conference despite the current situation. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-818818 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-6.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="683" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-6.jpg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-6-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"> “I believe even after the lockdown has been totally lifted, some children would still not have access to learn for months coming and lack of interaction can easily lead to a build of frustration resulting in mental health issues. Hence, it is important to give these children a chance to educate themselves and interact with others whilst all COVID-19 protocols were duly observed.” <img class="aligncenter wp-image-818819 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-7.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="683" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-7.jpg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-7-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"> The conference took place over a period of 4 hours with strict COVID-19 protocols and regulations at each venue such as, checking temperatures on arrival, social distancing stickers on the floor and a Medplus pharmacy tent on standby for any emergencies. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-818820 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-8.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="683" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-8.jpg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-8-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"> The participants were brought together as teams comprising of twenty members each, using colour White, Green, Yellow and Blue. The conference was also supported by 54gene, AHH, Cadwell, Health Markets Africa, The Alafia Foundation, Adara Foundation and Medplus Pharmacy as the lead sponsor. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-818821 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-9.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="683" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-9.jpg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Image-9-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"> Medplus Limited was incorporated as the first-ever retail pharmaceutical company in Nigeria in 1993, and has continued to proffer solutions to the challenge posed in accessing quality, genuine healthcare and beauty products in Nigeria.